frameDefinitions: A Manner describes general or specific characteristics of an event in one of three ways:  First, it can refer to how a Comparison_event transpires, absent the influence of an entity (e.g. 'the way you talk').
A Ratifier responds to a Proposal constructed by another party to make it binding over the Ratifier's jurisdiction or constituency.
An Agent displays a Characteristic of a Standard in his or her own way of behaving.
This frame concerns a specific subset of Instances of a Type which are evaluated in terms of their similarity to a conceptual prototype of the Type.
This frame involves a Creator making a duplicate, the Copy, of some Original entity.
In this frame a Profiled_item is higher that its Standard_item on a scale with respect to some Attribute.
frameExamples: He completed the task in a fervent <t>manner</t>.
The <t>ratification</t> of the Kyoto protocol has been a long, hard slog.
I guessed he was trying to <t>imitate</t> the movements of a skier
The teacher <t>copied</t> the problem onto the blackboard.
Notices for the Shield Theater's production of Macbeth <t>surpassed</t> all previous reviews .
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Comparison_event</fen> is the principal event being characteriszed by the <fen>Manner</fen>. The <fen>Manner</fen> of this <fen>Comparison_event</fen> is often used in comparison with the <fen>Foreground_event</fen>.
The <fen>Salient_entity</fen> that is associated with or directly responsible for the <fen>Comparison_activity</fen>.
The description of the <fen>Comparison_event</fen> or <fen>Comparison_activity</fen>.
A description of the <fen>Manner</fen>.
The <fen>Salient_entity</fen> conducts or engages in the <fen>Comparison_activity</fen> that is being described.

The individual or body that confirms a Proposal negotiated or created by another party, causing it to become binding in a jurisdiction represented by the <fen>Ratifier</fen>.  In the case of direct democratic ratification, the jurisdiction and the <fen>Ratifier</fen> are the same.
The idea or course of action proposed by another individual or body which the <fen>Ratifier</fen> endorses and makes binding.
The <fen>Time</fen> is when the <fen>Ratifier</fen> makes the <fen>Proposal</fen> binding.
The <fen>Place</fen> is where the <fen>Ratifier</fen> ratifies the <fen>Proposal</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person that borrows a <fen>Characteristic</fen> behavior from a <fen>Standard</fen>.
The <fen>Characteristic</fen> is a behavior or property that the <fen>Standard</fen> possesses and which the <fen>Agent</fen> adopts in his or her own behavior.
The <fen>Standard</fen> is the entity that exhibits a certain <fen>Characteristic</fen> that the <fen>Agent</fen> models their own behavior on.
The time at which the imitation occurs.
The location where the <fen>Agent</fen> imitates some entity which acts as a <fen>Standard</fen>.
A thing or episode that is considered exemplary of a certain <fen>Type</fen>.
The category of things or events from which an <fen>Instance</fen> is picked out.
The <fen>Creator</fen> produces the <fen>Copy</fen> based on the <fen>Original</fen>.  It is normally expressed as an External Argument.
The <fen>Original</fen> is the entity which is copied. With verbs it is frequently expressed as an NP Object:
The <fen>Copy</fen> produced by the <fen>Creator</fen> is frequently not expressed. However, when <fen>Copy</fen> does occur, it is usually expressed as the External Argument of verbs:
When the event occurs.
Where the event takes <fen>Place</fen>.
The role <fen>Standard_item</fen> denotes the entities that are exceeded by the <fen>Item</fen> with regard to the <fen>Attribute</fen>.
The <fen>Profiled_item</fen> is the entity that is located closest to the end of the scale evoked by some <fen>Attribute</fen>.
The <fen>Attribute</fen> is a property that evokes a scale along which the <fen>Item</fen> is located closer to one extreme in  comparison to the <fen>Standard_item</fen>.
The <fen>Standard_attribute</fen> is used when the standard is a specific value on  a scale.
The <fen>Profiled_attribute</fen> is a particular value on a scale which is being compared to an <fen>Attribute</fen> or <fen>Standard_item</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Item</fen> is higher on the scale than the <fen>Standard</fen>.
listRoleExamples: If <fex>we</fex> ratify Management 's plan , we 'll have to take a drug test every week !
President Aleksander Kwasniewski ratified <fex>protocols to the Europol Convention</fex>.
Mimic Snotlings do n't really think for themselves, <fex>they</fex> merely mimic the actions of Orcs and Goblins around them.
The singer says Gwen has copied <fex>her</fex> in many different ways.
<fex>The results</fex> replicate those of an earlier study.
In her time, she outstripped <fex>most politician in the country</fex>.
<fex>The buildings</fex> were outstripped in beauty and grace many years ago.
